Postoperative Care for cesarean.
1. you should avoid lifting anything heavier than your baby, and avoid most housework.
2. Make certain that you are getting plenty of fluids to keep you hydrated, and eat healthy meals to restore your energy and prevent constipation.
3. Have changing stations and feeding supplies close to you so that you do not have to get up too often.
4. Be alert to any fever or pain, which can both be signs of infection.
5. avoid sexual intercourse until your health care provider tells you that it is safe